article.description: — Kadary Richmond had 14 points in Seton Hall's 85-55 victory against Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday night.
article.headline: Richmond scores 14 as Seton Hall knocks off Fairleigh Dickinson 85-55
article.linkText: Richmond scores 14 as Seton Hall knocks off Fairleigh Dickinson 85-55
article.story: SOUTH ORANGE, N.J. -- — Kadary Richmond had 14 points in Seton Hall's 85-55 victory against Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday night. Richmond also contributed seven rebounds and four steals for the Pirates (2-0). Al-Amir Dawes was 5 of 15 shooting (3 for 10 from 3-point range) to add 13 points. Jaden Bediako shot 4 of 5 from the field and 4 for 4 from the line to finish with 12 points. The Knights (2-1) were led in scoring by Terrence Brown, who finished with 10 points. Fairleigh Dickinson also got eight points and three steals from Jameel Morris. In addition, Jo'el Emanuel finished with seven points. NEXT UP Both teams play again on Wednesday. Seton Hall hosts Albany (NY) and Fairleigh Dickinson hosts Saint Peter's. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
